<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,973,1575]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[189,253,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Q. Dai, J. K. Liu &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2014" box="[267,545,1369,1395]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="neopustulans">
<emphasis box="[267,545,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Roussoella neopustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphogically similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[858,996,1369,1395]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pustulans">
<emphasis box="[858,996,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R. pustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having smaller ascospores (11−12.5 × 3.5−4.5 µm vs. 10–16 × 4–5 µm) and larger asci (80−95 × 5.5−6.5 µm vs. 68–83 × 6.5–8.5 µm). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Q. Dai, J. K. Liu &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2014" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="neopustulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R. neopustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ascospore striations extend along the entire length and are linear, while those in 
<taxonomicName box="[1267,1407,1441,1467]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pustulans">
<emphasis box="[1267,1407,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R. pustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are shorter and irregular (
<bibRefCitation author="Hyde, K. D." box="[377,505,1477,1503]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="609 - 616" refId="ref17422" refString="Hyde, K. D. (1997) The genus Roussoella, including two new species from palms in Cuyabeno, Ecuador. Mycological Research 101: 609 - 616. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0953756296003061" type="journal article" year="1997">Hyde 1997</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Q. Dai, J. K. Liu &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2014" box="[524,801,1477,1503]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="neopustulans">
<emphasis box="[524,801,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Roussoella neopustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically distinct (
<collectionCode box="[1121,1186,1477,1503]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">FIGS</collectionCode>
. 1, 2) from 
<taxonomicName box="[1314,1451,1477,1503]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pustulans">
<emphasis box="[1314,1451,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R. pustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[143,221,1513,1539]" country="Fiji" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9fa9-21xc" name="Colo-i-Suva Silvicultural Station" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">MAFF</collectionCode>
239638). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Q. Dai, J. K. Liu &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2014" box="[336,614,1513,1539]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="neopustulans">
<emphasis box="[336,614,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Roussoella neopustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also a phylogenetically distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1204,1514,1539]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis box="[1063,1204,1514,1539]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R. siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[1219,1284,1513,1539]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">FIGS</collectionCode>
. 1, 2), but they are difficult to distinguish morphologically.
</paragraph>
